The [[2020 United States census]] counted 1827 residents living in Long Valley. In the CDP there is an estimated 800 total households living in 713 housing units. The racial makeup was 86.3% (1577) [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.8% (15) [[Black (U.S. Census)|Black or African American]], 2% (44) [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 2.2% (41) [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.0005% (1) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], and 8.9% (164) from [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census|other races]] and [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census|two or more races]]. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 8.2% (151) of the population.<ref name=":0">{{cite web|title=ACS Demographic and Housing Estimates|url=https://data.census.gov/profile/Long_Valley_CDP,_New_Jersey?g=160XX00US3441400#race-and-ethnicity|accessdate=August 21, 2025|website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

In Long Valley, the median age is 38.2 years old. About 12.5% (275) of the population is under the age of five, 67.2% (1,479) is between the ages of 18 and 64 and 11.4% (447) of the population are 65 or older.<ref name=":1">{{cite web|title=Long Valley CDP, New Jersey|url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/profile?g=1600000US3441400|accessdate=May 2, 2021|website=data.census.org}}</ref> 50.5% of the population was male, 49.5% of the population is female.<ref name=":0" />

The median income for a household in Long Valley is $104,722. The median income for males in Long Valley is $96,369, while the median income for females is $80,417.<ref name=":1" />

Of the population, 21.1% have some form of a high school degree, 17.4% have some college but no degree, 9.5% have an associate degree, 26% have a bachelor's degree and 20.9% have a graduate or professional degree.<ref name=":1" />

===2010 census===
The [[2010 United States census]] counted 1,879 people, 675 households, and 534 families in the CDP. The [[population density]] was {{convert|411.5|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|people&nbsp;|people|}}. There were 709 housing units at an average density of {{convert|155.3|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}. The racial makeup was 94.73% (1,780) [[White (U.S. census)|White]], 0.53% (10) [[Black (U.S. census)|Black or African American]], 0.00% (0) [[Native American (U.S. census)|Native American]], 1.81% (34) [[Asian (U.S. census)|Asian]], 0.00% (0) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. census)|Pacific Islander]], 1.33% (25) from [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census|other races]], and 1.60% (30) from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. census)|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 5.32% (100) of the population.<ref name=Census2010>[http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US3441400 DP-1 - Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 Demographic Profile Data for Long Valley CDP, New Jersey] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.today/20200212133306/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US3441400 |date=2020-02-12 }}, [[United States Census Bureau]]. Accessed December 23, 2012.</ref>

Of the 675 households, 37.0% had children under the age of 18; 65.8% were married couples living together; 9.5% had a female householder with no husband present and 20.9% were non-families. Of all households, 15.6% were made up of individuals and 6.1% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.77 and the average family size was 3.10.<ref name=Census2010/>

25.8% of the population were under the age of 18, 5.9% from 18 to 24, 21.0% from 25 to 44, 34.0% from 45 to 64, and 13.4% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 43.8 years. For every 100 females, the population had 97.2 males. For every 100 females ages 18 and older there were 96.5 males.<ref name=Census2010/>

